<TEXT>
vice president salvador laurel said 
saturday that doctors fear ferdinand marcos has lost the will to 
live has only a 10 percent chance of surviving the year and wants 
to die in his own country 
laurel spoke to reporters after returning from honolulu where 
the ousted philippine president accused of plundering billions from 
his homeland is in exile 
he said he would seek a meeting immediately with president 
corazon aquino to relay marcos wish and appeal to her sense of 
christian values to allow the former president to come home to die 
mrs aquino has refused to allow marcos or members of his family 
to return from hawaii where they have lived since a popular 
uprising toppled his 20year administration in february 1986 
laurel said doctors in honolulu told him that marcos might not 
survive the trip to the philippines but that the former president 
would prefer to die on the plane rather than on foreign soil 
a newspaper in the philippines quoted a cabinet official as 
saying saturday that the government has decided not to allow marcos 
to return and would even bar his body from being sent back after he 
dies 
the philippine daily inquirer quoted cabinet secretary jose de 
jesus as saying the government feared marcos supporters would try 
to destabilize the aquino administration if their leader came home 
we cant risk the gains by any destabilization effort which 
could derail us de jesus was quoted as saying 
the newspaper quoted unidentified government sources as saying 
the cabinet considered allowing marcos to return to laoag capital 
of his home province of ilocos norte about 250 miles north of 
manilabut the idea was rejected because of fears marcos would not 
honor the restriction the paper said 
laurel visited marcos hospital bedside thursday without mrs 
aquinos blessing 
marcos 71 remained in critical condition friday in st francis 
medical centers intensive care unit but an attorney said marcos 
was buoyed by laurels visit and doctors said his fever had subsided 
laurel declined to disclose details of his conversations with 
marcos his doctors and his wife imelda 
whatever our past differences and conflicts the reality is 
that the crisis in this mans life can seriously affect political 
stability of the philippines now is the time for compassion and 
forgiveness in order to achieve much needed unity among all 
filipinos laurel said in a statement thursday night 
marcos and his wife are under us indictment for allegedly 
plundering the philippines of more than 100 million and stashing 
much of the money in the united states 
when laurel was asked whether marcos would ever return to his 
homeland he repliedthats up to her referring to mrs aquino 
marcos son ferdinand jr said he relayed a letter to mrs 
aquino asking that his father be allowed to return mrs aquino who 
has repeatedly refused to allow marcos to return said she had not 
received the letter 
i can just make a decision once i know what the letter is all 
about she told the associated press in manila 
laurel conceded his was a personal not official visit but said 
he would make a full report to mrs aquino 
marcos was breathing with the assistance of a respirator 
following emergency surgery wednesday to reduce fluids building up 
in his lungs hospital spokeswoman norma kop said marcos was alert 
but unable to talk because of the respirator 
marcos was admitted to the hospital jan 15 for treatment of 
pneumonia and bronchial asthma in december he was hospitalized 
twice with congestive heart failure 
the marcoses would need permission from the us attorney general 
and the us district court in new york to leave the united states 
according to assistant us attorney charles labella the prosecutor 
in the us governments racketeering case against marcos and his 
wife 
a federal judge in new york is to decide this month whether 
marcos is healthy enough to stand trial on criminal racketeering 
charges mrs marcos pleaded innocent and is free on 5 million bail 
</TEXT>
