correct inaccuracies about them in the news media corrections would 
have to be given the same prominence as the original mistake 
worthington said his right of reply bill was needed because of 
what he called the deterioration in standards of some sections of 
the press 
he said the bill which was unopposed friday in its second 
reading was not an attack on press freedom but an attack on the few 
editors and proprietors who abused their power 
legislators said the government was neutral about the right of 
reply bill so it would not have any priority on the crowded 
parliamentary agenda they said time was likely to run out before 
