soviet foreign minister eduard shevardnadze ended 
a threeday visit to china on saturday by announcing the nations 
will hold their first summit in 30 years in midmay 
shevardnadze said soviet president mikhail gorbachev will travel 
to beijing at the invitation of the chinese for a meeting with 
senior leader deng xiaoping soviet sources who spoke on condition 
of anonymity said the summit was tentatively scheduled for may 15 
chinas deputy foreign minister tian zengpei however said no 
date had been set and that the chinese were studying the 
proposal for the may meeting 
shevardnadze later flew to islamabad pakistan for meetings with 
pakistani leaders about the soviet troop withdrawal from neighboring 
afghanistan 
at a news conference before his departure shevardnadze said deng 
told him the summit would close the page on the past and open up a 
chapter on the future 
in a move toward complete normalization of relations 
diplomats and other officials are to discuss reducing military 
tensions along the 5000mile sovietchinese border he said 
western diplomats said the issue first came up when chinese 
foreign minister qian qichen visited moscow in december 
we hope at the summit we will be able to make progress in that 
important direction shevardnadze said 
he said the first step might be an agreement on advance notice of 
troop movements and military exercises and then negotiations for 
disbanding offensive forces 
in the 1950s china depended on soviet technical and military aid 
and followed the soviet lead in diplomatic policy relations between 
the countries soured in 1960 over ideological and strategic 
disputes and they fought a brief border war in 1969 
the chinese agreed to discuss a summit last year after progress 
was made on what they call the three obstacles border 
tensions soviet aid for vietnams invasion of cambodia and the 
soviet intervention in afghanistan 
the last soviet troops are supposed to be out of afghanistan by 
feb 15 
gorbachev has pledged to remove from asia 200000 soviet troops 
many now stationed along the chinese border and has said that most 
of moscows 50000 troops in mongolia will be withdrawn 
qian was the first chinese foreign minister to visit moscow in 32 
years shevardnadzes visit was the first by a soviet foreign 
minister in 30 years and was designed to lay the groundwork for the 
summit 
china formally issued its invitation to gorbachev on friday 
substantive progress has been made on obstacles that have 
stood in the way of a summit deputy foreign minister tian told 
reporters following shevardnadzes departure this visit produced 
results 
he said the two sides now agree that vietnam should end its 
10year occupation of cambodia by september as promised and that 
there should be international supervision of the troop withdrawal 
china backs the antivietnamese resistance in cambodia and has 
demanded moscow pressure its ally vietnam to pull out 
shevardnadze said better sinosoviet relations are the result of 
the countries economic reforms and he envisioned increased trading 
between the nations 
the countries are believed to want to ease tensions so they can 
concentrate less on military matters and more on rejuvenating their 
economies 
shevardnadze flew to shanghai about 870 miles south of beijing 
for the 90minute meeting with deng on saturday morning 
he said chinas top leader was a very wise man who has a lot of 
rich experience 
there have been rumors that the 84yearold deng is in failing 
health but shevardnadze said he appeared quite fit 
