reject the proposed congressional pay raise and roll back the 
increase if the house lets it become law by ducking a vote 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
house opponents of the congressional pay raise say they cant 
stop the increase despite growing opposition in the senate 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
president bush endorses the proposed pay raise saying the 
increase is overdue theres no question about it the president 
says some elements bothered him but points out that 
congressional procedure on pay raises leaves us with either the 
commission recommendation or nothing 
</TEXT>
