debt has endangered the pensions of city employees who will retire 
in the future 
the city has been diverting motor fuel tax money that it gets 
from the state in october the state cut off the money and ordered 
the city to repay about 3 million that state audits determined the 
city had misused 
someone has been forging the signature of city treasurer 
charlotte moore on sewer lien releases thousands of dollars that 
should have been paid to the treasurers office and put into the 
citys coffers have never arrived moore told state police 
legality does not seem to be a concern here at city hall 
moore said after the raid its a great concern of mine when 
people are using my signature and its not my signature 
